sg.danielneutrinos.jmdictlib.data

Class Sense

  • java.lang.Object
    • sg.danielneutrinos.jmdictlib.data.Sense

  • public class Sense
extends java.lang.Object
    Translational equivalent of the Japanese word, plus other related information. Where there are several distinctly different meanings of the word, multiple sense objects will be employed

    • Field Detail

      • invalidSenseKanjis

        private java.util.List<java.lang.String> invalidSenseKanjis
        If present, indicate that the sense is restricted to Kanji

      • invalidSenseReadings

        private java.util.List<java.lang.String> invalidSenseReadings
        If present, indicate that the sense is restricted to Reading

      • xReferences

        private java.util.List<java.lang.String> xReferences
        Cross-reference to another entry with a similar or related meaning or sense. In some cases a keb will be followed by a reb and/or a sense number to provide a precise target for the cross-reference. Where this happens, a JIS "centre-dot" (0x2126) is placed between the components of the cross-reference. The target keb or reb must not contain a centre-dot.

      • antonyms

        private java.util.List<java.lang.String> antonyms
        Indicates another entry which is an antonym of the current entry/sense. The content of this element must exactly match that of a keb or reb element in another entry.

      • partsOfSpeech

        private java.util.List<java.lang.String> partsOfSpeech
        In general where there are multiple senses in an entry, the part-of-speech of an earlier sense will apply to later senses unless there is a new part-of-speech indicated.

      • fields

        private java.util.List<java.lang.String> fields
        Information about the field of application of the entry/sense. When absent, general application is implied.

      • misc

        private java.util.List<java.lang.String> misc
        Used for other relevant information about the entry/sense. As with part-of-speech, information will usually apply to several senses.

      • sourceLanguages

        private java.util.List<SourceLanguage> sourceLanguages
        Information about the source language(s) of a loan-word/gairaigo.

      • dialects

        private java.util.List<java.lang.String> dialects
        For words specifically associated with regional dialects in Japanese

      • glosses

        private java.util.List<Gloss> glosses
        Target-language words or phrases which are equivalents to the Japanese word. Would normally be present, however it may be omitted in entries which are purely for a cross-reference.

      • info

        private java.lang.String info
        Additional information to be recorded about a sense. Typical usage would be to indicate such things as level of currency of a sense, the regional variations, etc.
